@prefix narr: <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .

GRAPH <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_Narrative_B2CPivot> {
  <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_Narrative_B2CPivot> a narr:Digest ;
    narr:digestOf <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_B2CPivot> ;
    narr:childCount "9"^^xsd:integer ;
    narr:generatedFrom "d879eb328ac61ec3c7dc327bc455342c7ffc2650" ;
    narr:narration """The trajectory of aswritten’s market positioning has shifted from a binary choice between B2B and B2C toward a unified model of individual-led growth. Following the initial [B2C primary-market convergence](narr:Position_B2CPrimaryMarket) in March 2026, the animating thesis held that [AI has made every individual their own team](narr:Position_EveryIndividualIsTheirOwnTeam), effectively turning the solopreneur into the primary unit of value. This was complemented by the observation that [AI has restored individual contributor status](narr:Position_AIRestoredICStatus), shifting the professional focus back to strategy and curation. While an [open question](narr:Position_SMBPivotReconciliationNeeded) in April highlighted friction between this volume-B2C pivot and an enterprise-style engagement pattern, Scarlet later proposed that [Expert, Team, and Org are a continuum of one use case](narr:Narrative_TierContinuumNotDistinctMarkets). This framework asserts that organizational tiers do not supersede the B2C framing; rather, the solo Expert tier serves as the natural on-ramp. Most recently, the pivot has been grounded in [founder-fit](narr:Position_FounderFitNarrativeEdge), with the recognition that [B2B defaults were career artifacts](narr:Position_B2BDefaultCareerArtifact) rather than strategic requirements. The current operational focus is the [individuation curve](narr:Narrative_IndividuationCurveConversionMechanic), mapping how users progress from generic engagement to ownership.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_IndividuationCurveConversionMechanic> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_TierContinuumNotDistinctMarkets> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_AIRestoredICStatus> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_B2BDefaultCareerArtifact> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_B2CPrimaryMarket> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_EnterpriseDoesNotSupersedB2C> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_EveryIndividualIsTheirOwnTeam> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_FounderFitNarrativeEdge> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_SMBPivotReconciliationNeeded> ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "AI has made every individual their own team" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_EveryIndividualIsTheirOwnTeam> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "AI has made everyone individual contributors again" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_AIRestoredICStatus> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "Expert, Team, and Org tiers are a continuum of one use case" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_TierContinuumNotDistinctMarkets> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "B2B default is an artifact of her career history" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_B2BDefaultCareerArtifact> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "conversion mechanic is own-by-default, pay-to-continue" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_IndividuationCurveConversionMechanic> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "The 'enterprise-shape' engagement pattern may be orthogonal to organizational size, potentially complicating the B2C/B2B divide." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_SMBPivotReconciliationNeeded> ] ;
    narr:writer "google/gemini-3.1-flash-lite" .
}